column5: Field Label

TRAINING. Coordinator:� All instructions to you (the coordinator) begin with �Coordinator:�; otherwise, all instructions are to be posed to the study participant. On each of the following screens (not including instructional screens like this one), check �BUZZ� if the device being tested buzzed between the time the participant starts and stops a directed action. Otherwise tap �NO BUZZ�.
I will ask you to perform different actions with your right hand. Please try to act naturally as you perform each of the actions.� We�ll start by calibrating the devices on your wrist.
Coordinator:� TRAINING MODEL #1 sitting upright: Keen ON, GRD OFF; Train the Keen on the following 4 behaviors sitting upright (GRD already pre-trained on these behaviors).
First, pretend to scratch or pull hair on the back of your head until I tell you to stop.
Now pretend to scratch or pull hair on the right side of your head above your ear until I tell you to stop.
Now pretend to pull your right eyelash until I tell you to stop.
Now pretend to bite your nails until I tell you to stop.
Coordinator: TRAINING MODEL #1 sitting upright: Keen ON, GRD OFF; Train the Keen on the following behavior in 3 positions (GRD already pre-trained on this behavior).
Once again, pretend to bite your nails until I tell you to stop.
Now lean back and look up at the ceiling and pretend to bite your nails until I tell you to stop.
Finally, lie on your left side and pretend to bite your nails until I tell you to stop.
TEST. Coordinator:� TEST MODEL #1 sitting upright: Group A: Keen ON, GRD OFF; Group B: Keen OFF, GRD ON
